<title type="html"><![CDATA[4/8 (Thu.) Asia's first 'travel bubble' opens/Passenger train carrying 490 derails in Taiwan (Host: Julia)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=487&amp;p=509#p509"><![CDATA[
April 8, 2021 (Thu.) Asia's first 'travel bubble' opens between Taiwan and Palau/Passenger train carrying 490 derails in Taiwan (Host: Julia)<br /><br /><span style="color: #BF0000">Place: 丹堤咖啡, 台北市延平南路107號2樓 (MRT 西門站4號出口)<br />Agenda:<br />07:00-7:05 pm Opening Remarks<br />07:05-7:40 pm Session 1 Group Discussion<br />07:40-8:00 pm Presentation (At least two members of each table are invited, 2 mins / each member)<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:40 pm Session 2 discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Presentation</span><br /><br />Session 1. Asia's first 'travel bubble' opens between Taiwan and Palau<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://edition.cnn.com/travel/article/taiwan-palau-travel-bubble-intl-hnk/index.html">https://edition.cnn.com/travel/article/ ... index.html</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br />1.How do you like the “travel bubble”? Are you interested in trying it now or waiting for the end of Covid-19 to travel abroad?<br />2.Besides Palau, what other countries do you expect to open a reciprocal travel lane with Taiwan? Why?<br />3.What do you think about the restrictions on the travel bubble: arrive five and a half hours early to test Covid-19 on the airport, stick to strict itineraries, and wear a mask in public?<br />4.Do you think the package is too expensive or worth the cost?<br /><br />Session 2. Passenger train carrying 490 derails in Taiwan, killing at least 50 and injuring dozens <br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://edition.cnn.com/2021/04/01/asia/taiwan-train-derail-intl-hnk/index.html">https://edition.cnn.com/2021/04/01/asia ... index.html</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions: <br />1.What are the most dangerous ways of transportation? Why?<br />2.“Most vehicle crashes, and the majority of all transportation-related injuries and fatalities, are caused by human error.” Do you agree on the saying?  Why or why not?<br />3.To what extent, do you agree that life is unpredictable? What are your ways to reduce or respond to uncertainty of life?<br />4.Living in the present/stopping worrying about tomorrow, and cherishing/being grateful to the people around us usually come out of our mind when a serious disaster occurs. Do you practice these ideas in your daily life? If yes, please provide us with some examples.<br /><br /><br /><span style="color: #BF0000">P.S.<br />1.因聚會地點是在咖啡店內，所以有低消80元喔。<br />2.參加三次後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />3.請帶著開放與熱情來參加自由的全英文會話聚會~</span><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=37037">JuliaHo</a> — Sun Apr 04, 2021 8:07 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
